Hash: SHA1

SUPPORT COMMUNICATION - SECURITY BULLETIN

Document ID: c00657001
Version: 2

HPSBUX02115 SSRT061077 rev.2 - HP-UX running Support Tools Manager (xstm, cstm, stm) 
Local Denial of Service (DoS)

NOTICE: The information in this Security Bulletin should be acted upon as soon as possible.

Release Date: 2006-08-14
Last Updated: 2006-08-15

Potential Security Impact: Local Denial of Service (DoS)

Source: Hewlett-Packard Company, HP Software Security Response Team

VULNERABILITY SUMMARY
A potential security vulnerability has been identified with HP-UX running 
Support Tools Manager (xstm, cstm, stm). The vulnerability could be exploited 
by a local user to create a Denial of Service (DoS).

References: none

SUPPORTED SOFTWARE VERSIONS*: ONLY impacted versions are listed.
HP-UX B.11.11, B.11.23

BACKGROUND

Hewlett-Packard Company has become aware of a potential vulnerability in the 
Support Tool Manager (STM) application, typically used for hardware diagnostic purposes.

To determine if an HP-UX system has an affected version, 
search the output of "swlist -a revision -l fileset" for one 
of the filesets listed below. For affected systems verify 
that the recommended action has been taken.

AFFECTED VERSIONS

HP-UX B.11.11
==========
 ->Sup-Tool-Mgr.STM-SHLIBS,revision=B.11.11.13.14
 ->Sup-Tool-Mgr.STM-SHLIBS,revision=B.11.11.14.15
 ->Sup-Tool-Mgr.STM-SHLIBS,revision=B.11.11.15.13
 ->action: install revision B.11.11.17.02 or subsequent
URL: http://software.hp.com/portal/swdepot/displayProductInfo.do?productNumber=B6191AAE

HP-UX B.11.11
==========
 ->Sup-Tool-Mgr.STM-SHLIBS,revision=B.11.11.16.09
action: install PHSS_34288 or subsequent

HP-UX B.11.23
==========
Sup-Tool-Mgr.STM-SHLIBS
action: install revision B.11.23.07.04 or subsequent
URL: http://software.hp.com/portal/swdepot/displayProductInfo.do?productNumber=B6191AAE

END AFFECTED VERSIONS

RESOLUTION

HP is providing the following to resolve this potential vulnerability.

 ->HP-UX B.11.11
============

STM Version  Distribution SW Depot ID    Resolution

A.43.00        HWE0312    B.11.11.13.14  Install revision B.11.11.17.02 or subsequent
A.45.00        HWE0406    B.11.11.14.15  Install revision B.11.11.17.02 or subsequent
A.47.00        HWE0412    B.11.11.15.13  Install revision B.11.11.17.02 or subsequent
A.49.10        HWE0509    B.11.11.16.09  Install PHSS_34288 or subsequent

 ->PHSS_34288 can be downloaded from http://itrc.hp.com
 ->Revision B.11.11.17.02 (STM version A.52.00, HWE0606) is available here:
http://software.hp.com/portal/swdepot/displayProductInfo.do?productNumber=B6191AAE

 ->NOTE:
 ->Customers running STM version A.49.10 (revision B.11.11.16.09) can either install
 ->PHSS_34288 or install STM version A.52.00 (revision B.11.11.17.02) or subsequent.
 ->Customers running STM versions prior to version A.49.10 (revision B.11.11.16.09) must
 ->install STM version A.52.00 (revision B.11.11.17.02) or subsequent to resolve the issue.

HP-UX B.11.23
==========
For HP-UX B.11.23 running STM versions prior to C.53.00 (revision B.11.23.07.04)
Install STM version C.53.00 or subsequent

The update is available here:
http://software.hp.com/portal/swdepot/displayProductInfo.do?productNumber=B6191AAE

 ->For further information please refer to http://docs.hp.com/en/diag/stm/stm_upd.htm

MANUAL ACTIONS: Yes - Update

 ->HP-UX B.11.11 update to B.11.11.17.02, STM versions A.52.00 or subsequent
HP-UX B.11.23 update to B.11.23.07.04, STM version: C.53.00 or subsequent

PRODUCT SPECIFIC INFORMATION
HP-UX Security Patch Check: Security Patch Check revision B.02.00 analyzes 
all HP-issued Security Bulletins to provide a subset of recommended actions 
that potentially affect a specific HP-UX system. For more information: http://software.hp.com/portal/swdepot/displayProductInfo.do? productNumber=B6834AA

